Decathlon , the French sporting goods
retailer, is in talks to buy several of the 11 Best Buy stores
in the U.K. that are up for sale, the Sunday Telegraph reported,
without citing anyone.  Decathlon aims to raise its store count in the country to
100 outlets from 12, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
